                                "mergeField": "%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3EGuida%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Ence%20%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Efor%20Disclosure%202-6%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20to%202-6-a%3C/strong%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Sectors%20can%20be%20identified%20according%20to%20categories,%20such%20as%20the%20public%20or%20private%20sector;%20or%20industry-specific%20categories,%20such%20as%20the%20education%20sector%20or%20the%20financial%20sector.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Depending%20on%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20activities,%20sectors%20can%20be%20identified%20using%20the%20GRI%20Sector%20Standards%20or%20classification%20systems%20such%20as%20the%20Global%20Industry%20Classification%20Standard%20(GICS&reg;),%20the%20Industry%20Classification%20Benchmark%20(ICB),%20the%20International%20Standard%20Industrial%20Classification%20of%20All%20Economic%20Activities%20(ISIC),%20and%20the%20Sustainable%20Industry%20Classification%20System%20(SICS&reg;).%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Guidance%20to%202-6-b%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20The%20organization&rsquo;s%20value%20chain%20includes%20the%20range%20of%20activities%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20organization,%20and%20by%20entities%20upstream%20and%20downstream%20from%20the%20organization,%20to%20bring%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20products%20or%20services%20from%20their%20conception%20to%20their%20end%20use.%20Entities%20upstream%20from%20the%20organization%20provide%20products%20or%20services%20used%20in%20the%20development%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20own%20products%20or%20services.%20Entities%20downstream%20from%20the%20organization%20are%20those%20that%20receive%20products%20or%20services%20from%20the%20organization.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Entities%20in%20the%20value%20chain%20include%20entities%20beyond%20the%20first%20tier,%20both%20upstream%20and%20downstream.%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20information%20reported%20under%202-6-b%20provides%20a%20context%20for%20understanding%20the%20organization&rsquo;s&nbsp;impacts%20across%20its%20value%20chain,%20including%20through%20the%20use%20of%20its%20products%20and%20services.%20Describing%20the%20markets%20served%20provides%20further%20information%20on%20the%20groups%20of%20customers%20targeted%20by%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20products%20and%20services.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20The%20organization%20is%20not%20required%20to%20provide%20a%20detailed%20description%20of%20each%20activity%20in%20its%20value%20chain.%20Instead,%20it%20can%20provide%20a%20high-level%20overview%20of%20its%20value%20chain.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Guidance%20to%202-6-b-i%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20When%20describing%20its%20activities,%20the%20organization%20should%20report%20its%20total%20number%20of%20operations%20and%20explain%20how%20it%20defines%20&lsquo;operation&rsquo;.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20When%20describing%20its%20products%20and%20services,%20the%20organization%20should%20report:%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20quantity%20of%20products%20or%20services%20provided%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20(e.g.,%20number%20of%20products%20or%20services%20provided,%20net%20sales%20of%20products%20or%20services%20provided);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20Whether%20it%20sells%20products%20or%20services%20that%20are%20banned%20in%20certain%20markets%20or%20are%20the%20subject%20of%20stakeholder%20concerns%20or%20public%20debate,%20including%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20ban%20or%20concerns%20and%20how%20the%20organization%20has%20responded%20to%20these%20concerns.&nbsp;%20When%20describing%20the%20markets%20served,%20the%20organization%20can%20report:%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20geographic%20locations%20where%20products%20and%20services%20are%20offered;%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20demographic%20or%20other%20characteristics%20of%20the%20markets;%20&bull;%20Information%20on%20the%20size%20and%20relative%20importance%20of%20the%20markets%20(e.g.,%20net%20sales,%20net%20revenues).%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Guidance%20to%202-6-b-ii%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20describe:%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20types%20of%20suppliers%20(e.g.,%20brokers,%20contractors,%20wholesalers);%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E&bull;The%20estimated%20number%20of%20suppliers%20throughout%20its%20supply%20chain%20and%20in%20each%20tier%20(e.g.,%20first%20tier,%20second%20tier);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20types%20of%20activities%20related%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20products%20and%20services%20carried%20out%20by%20its%20suppliers%20(e.g.,%20manufacturing,%20providing%20consulting%20services);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20nature%20of%20its%20business%20relationships%20with%20its%20suppliers%20(e.g.,%20long-term%20or%20short-term,%20contractual%20or%20non-contractual,%20project-based%20or%20event-based);%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E&bull;The%20sector-specific%20characteristics%20of%20its%20supply%20chain%20(e.g.,%20labor-intensive);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20estimated%20monetary%20value%20of%20payments%20made%20to%20its%20suppliers;%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20geographic%20location%20of%20its%20suppliers.%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EGuidance%20to%202-6-b-iii%20%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20describe:%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E&bull;%20The%20types%20of%20downstream%20entities%20(e.g.,%20customers,%20beneficiaries);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20estimated%20number%20of%20downstream%20entities;%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;The%20types%20of%20activities%20related%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20products%20and%20services%20carried%20out%20by%20the%20downstream%20entities%20(e.g.,%20manufacturing,%20wholesale,%20retail);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20nature%20of%20its%20business%20relationships%20with%20the%20downstream%20entities%20(e.g.,%20long-term%20or%20short-term,%20contractual%20or%20non-contractual,%20project-based%20or%20event-based);%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20&bull;%20The%20geographic%20location%20of%20the%20downstream%20entities.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Guidance%20to%202-6-c%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Other%20relevant%20business%20relationships%20include%20relationships%20that%20the%20organization%20has%20with%20entities%20that%20are%20not%20described%20as%20part%20of%20its%20value%20chain%20under%202-6-b.%20These%20may%20include%20business%20partners%20(e.g.,%20joint%20ventures)%20and%20other%20entities%20directly%20linked%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20operations,%20products,%20or%20services%20(for%20examples,%20see%20the%20note%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20&lsquo;business%20relationships&rsquo;).%20%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20types%20of%20entities,%20their%20activities,%20and%20their%20geographic%20location.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3E%20Guidance%20to%202-6-d%20%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ERequirement%202-6-d%20entails%20describing%20significant%20changes%20in%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20sectors,%20value%20chain,%20and%20other%20business%20relationships%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20reporting%20period.%20This%20information%20can%20help%20explain%20changes%20to%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20impacts.%20Examples%20of%20significant%20changes%20that%20can%20be%20reported%20under%20this%20disclosure%20are%20changes%20in%20activities%20such%20as%20the%20opening,%20closing,%20or%20expansion%20of%20facilities;%20changes%20in%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20supply%20chain%20or%20in%20its%20relationships%20with%20suppliers,%20including%20selection%20and%20termination;%20or%20changes%20in%20the%20location%20of%20its%20suppliers.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3EGuida%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Ence&nbsp;%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Efor%20Disclosure%202-7%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ETogether%20with%20Disclosure%202-8,%20this%20disclosure%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20approach%20to%20employment,%20including%20the%20scope%20and%20nature%20of%20impacts%20arising%20from%20its%20employment%20practices.%20It%20also%20provides%20contextual%20information%20that%20aids%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20information%20reported%20in%20other%20disclosures,%20and%20serves%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20calculation%20in%20other%20disclosures,%20such%20as%20Disclosure%202-21%20Annual%20total%20compensation%20ratio%20and%20Disclosure%202-30%20Collective%20bargaining%20agreements%20in%20this%20Standard.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThis%20disclosure%20covers%20all%20employees%20who%20perform%20work%20for%20any%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20entities%20included%20in%20its%20sustainability%20reporting%20as%20reported%20under%20Disclosure%202-2%20in%20this%20Standard.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EGuidance%20to%202-7-a%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EAn%20employee%20is%20an%20individual%20who%20is%20in%20an%20employment%20relationship%20with%20the%20organization%20according%20to%20national%20law%20or%20practice.Providing%20a%20breakdown%20of%20employees%20by%20gender%20gives%20insight%20into%20gender%20representation%20across%20the%20organization.%20Providing%20a%20breakdown%20of%20employees%20by%20region%20gives%20insight%20into%20regional%20variations.%20A%20region%20can%20refer%20to%20a%20country%20or%20other%20geographic%20locations,%20such%20as%20a%20city%20or%20a%20world%20region.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ESee%20Table%201%20and%20Table%202%20of%20this%20Standard%20for%20examples%20of%20how%20to%20present%20this%20information.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EGuidance%20to%202-7-b%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20definitions%20of%20permanent,%20temporary,%20non-guaranteed%20hours,%20full-time,%20and%20part-time%20employees%20differ%20between%20countries.%20If%20the%20organization%20has%20employees%20in%20more%20than%20one%20country,%20it%20should%20use%20the%20definitions%20as%20per%20the%20national%20laws%20of%20the%20countries%20where%20the%20employees%20are%20based%20to%20calculate%20country-level%20data.%20The%20country-level%20data%20should%20then%20be%20added%20up%20to%20calculate%20total%20numbers,%20disregarding%20differences%20in%20national%20legal%20definitions.Non-guaranteed%20hours%20employees%20are%20employed%20by%20the%20organization%20without%20a%20guarantee%20of%20a%20minimum%20or%20fixed%20number%20of%20working%20hours.%20The%20employee%20may%20need%20to%20make%20themselves%20available%20for%20work%20as%20required,%20but%20the%20organization%20is%20not%20contractually%20obligated%20to%20offer%20the%20employee%20a%20minimum%20or%20fixed%20number%20of%20working%20hours%20per%20day,%20week,%20or%20month.%20Casual%20employees,%20employees%20with%20zero-hour%20contracts,%20and%20on-call%20employees%20are%20examples%20that%20fall%20under%20this%20category.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EIf%20the%20organization%20is%20unable%20to%20report%20exact%20figures,%20it%20can%20report%20estimates%20of%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20to%20the%20nearest%20ten%20or,%20where%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20is%20greater%20than%201,000,%20to%20the%20nearest%20100,%20and%20explain%20this%20under%202-7-c.See%20Table%201%20and%20Table%202%20of%20this%20Standard%20for%20examples%20of%20how%20to%20present%20this%20information.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EGuidance%20to%202-7-c%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20total%20number%20of%20employees%20and%20the%20number%20of%20permanent,%20temporary,%20non-guaranteed%20hours,%20full-time,%20and%20part-time%20employees%20in%20head%20count%20or%20full-time%20equivalent%20(FTE).%20Reporting%20these%20numbers%20in%20head%20count%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20number%20of%20individual%20employees,%20whether%20full-time%20or%20part-time%20employed.%20Reporting%20these%20numbers%20in%20FTE%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20hours%20worked.%20The%20organization%20can%20use%20another%20methodology%20for%20reporting%20these%20numbers.Reporting%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20reporting%20period%20provides%20information%20for%20that%20point%20in%20time,%20without%20capturing%20fluctuations%20during%20the%20reporting%20period.%20Reporting%20these%20numbers%20in%20averages%20across%20the%20reporting%20period%20takes%20into%20account%20fluctuations%20during%20the%20reporting%20period.Guidance%20to%202-7-d%20Quantitative%20data,%20such%20as%20the%20number%20of%20temporary%20or%20part-time%20employees,%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20sufficient%20on%20its%20own.%20For%20example,%20a%20high%20proportion%20of%20temporary%20or%20part-time%20employees%20could%20indicate%20lack%20of%20employment%20security%20for%20employees,%20but%20it%20could%20equally%20signal%20workplace%20flexibility%20when%20offered%20as%20a%20voluntary%20choice.%20For%20this%20reason,%20the%20organization%20is%20required%20to%20report%20contextual%20information%20to%20help%20information%20users%20interpret%20the%20data.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20explain%20the%20reasons%20for%20temporary%20employment.%20An%20example%20of%20such%20a%20reason%20is%20the%20recruitment%20of%20employees%20to%20undertake%20work%20on%20a%20temporary%20or%20seasonal%20project%20or%20event.%20Another%20example%20is%20the%20standard%20practice%20to%20offer%20a%20temporary%20contract%20(e.g.,%20six%20months)%20to%20new%20employees%20before%20an%20offer%20of%20permanent%20employment%20is%20made.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20explain%20the%20reasons%20for%20non-guaranteed%20hours%20employment.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EThe%20organization%20can%20explain%20how%20it%20defines%20full-time%20employment.%20If%20the%20organization%20has%20employees%20in%20more%20than%20one%20country,%20it%20can%20report%20the%20definitions%20of%20full-time%20employment%20it%20uses%20for%20the%20regions%20that%20cover%20these%20countries.%20The%20organization%20can%20also%20explain%20the%20reasons%20for%20part-time%20employment.%20Examples%20of%20such%20reasons%20are%20to%20accommodate%20employees&rsquo;%20requests%20to%20work%20reduced%20hours,%20or%20because%20the%20organization%20is%20unable%20to%20provide%20full-time%20employment%20to%20all%20employees.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EIf%20there%20are%20differences%20in%20permanent,%20temporary,%20non-guaranteed%20hours,%20full-time,%20and%20part-time%20employment%20between%20genders%20or%20between%20regions,%20the%20organization%20can%20explain%20the%20reasons%20for%20these%20differences.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EGuidance%20to%202-7-e%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ERequirement%202-7-e%20enables%20the%20organization%20to%20explain%20how%20the%20numbers%20of%20employees%20vary%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20reporting%20periods%20(i.e.,%20whether%20the%20numbers%20have%20increased%20or%20decreased).%20It%20can%20also%20include%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20fluctuations.%20For%20example,%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20could%20be%20due%20to%20a%20seasonal%20event.%20Conversely,%20a%20decrease%20in%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20reporting%20period%20could%20be%20due%20to%20the%20completion%20of%20a%20temporary%20project.%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3EIt%20is%20up%20to%20the%20organization%20to%20determine%20which%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20it%20considers%20significant%20to%20report%20under%202-7-e.%20The%20organization%20should%20report%20its%20threshold%20for%20determining%20significant%20fluctuations.If%20there%20are%20no%20significant%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20or%20between%20reporting%20periods,%20a%20brief%20statement%20of%20this%20fact%20is%20sufficient%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20requirement.&nbsp;%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2010pt;%22%3ETable%201.%20Example%20template%20for%20presenting%20information%20on%20employees%20by%20gender.%20Please%20See%20Relevant%20Tab%20For%20Diagram&nbsp;%3C/span%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3EGuida%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Ence&nbsp;%3C/span%3E%3Cspan%20style=%22font-size:%2012pt;%22%3Efor%20Disclosure%202-8%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThis%20disclosure%20provides%20an%20understanding%20of%20how%20much%20the%20organization%20relies%20on%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20to%20perform%20its%20work,%20in%20comparison%20to%20employees.%20This%20information%20is%20important%20for%20understanding%20how%20many%20workers%20in%20total%20perform%20work%20for%20the%20organization,%20because%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20are%20not%20represented%20in%20employment%20figures%20reported%20under%20Disclosure%202-7.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EDisclosure%202-8,%20together%20with%20Disclosure%202-7,%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20approach%20to%20employment,%20as%20well%20as%20the%20scope%20and%20nature%20of%20impacts%20arising%20from%20its%20employment%20practices.%20It%20also%20provides%20contextual%20information%20that%20aids%20an%20understanding%20of%20the%20information%20reported%20in%20other%20disclosures.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThis%20disclosure%20covers%20all%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20and%20whose%20work%20is%20controlled%20by%20any%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20entities%20included%20in%20its%20sustainability%20reporting%20as%20reported%20under%20Disclosure%202-2%20in%20this%20Standard.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20all%20the%20workers%20performing%20work%20for%20the%20organization%20are%20employees%20and%20the%20organization%20does%20not%20have%20any%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees,%20a%20brief%20statement%20of%20this%20fact%20is%20sufficient%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20requirements%20under%20this%20disclosure.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20to%202-8-a%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWorkers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20are%20those%20who%20perform%20work%20for%20the%20organization%20but%20are%20not%20in%20an%20employment%20relationship%20with%20the%20organization.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThis%20disclosure%20requires%20the%20organization%20to%20report%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20and%20whose%20work%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization.%20Control%20of%20work%20implies%20that%20the%20organization%20directs%20the%20work%20performed%20or%20has%20control%20over%20the%20means%20or%20methods%20for%20performing%20the%20work.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20might%20have%20sole%20control%20of%20the%20work%20or%20share%20control%20with%20one%20or%20more%20organizations%20(e.g.,%20suppliers,%20customers,%20or%20other%20business%20partners,%20such%20as%20in%20joint%20ventures).%20Types%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20and%20whose%20work%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization%20include%20agency%20workers,%20apprentices,%20contractors,%20home%20workers,%20interns,%20self-employed%20persons,%20sub-contractors,%20and%20volunteers.%20The%20organization%20should%20report%20how%20it%20has%20determined%20when%20it%20has%20control%20of%20the%20work%20for%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20following%20are%20examples%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20and%20whose%20work%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization.%20The%20following%20workers%20are%20included%20under%20this%20disclosure:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Contractors%20hired%20by%20the%20organization%20to%20perform%20work%20at%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20workplace,%20in%20a%20public%20area%20(e.g.,%20on%20a%20road),%20or%20directly%20at%20the%20workplace%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20client.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Workers%20of%20one%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20suppliers,%20where%20the%20organization%20instructs%20the%20supplier%20to%20use%20particular%20materials%20or%20work%20methods%20to%20manufacture%20the%20products%20or%20deliver%20the%20services.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Volunteers%20or%20interns%20performing%20work%20for%20the%20organization.The%20following%20are%20examples%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20and%20whose%20work%20is%20not%20controlled%20by%20the%20organization.%20The%20following%20workers%20are%20not%20included%20under%20this%20disclosure:%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Workers%20of%20an%20equipment%20supplier%20to%20the%20organization%20who%20perform%20regular%20maintenance%20on%20the%20supplier&rsquo;s%20equipment%20(e.g.,%20photocopy%20machines%20at%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20workplace)%20as%20stipulated%20in%20the%20contract%20between%20the%20equipment%20supplier%20and%20the%20organization.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&bull;%20Workers%20of%20one%20of%20the%20organization&rsquo;s%20suppliers,%20if%20the%20organization%20sources%20standard%20products%20manufactured%20using%20the%20supplier&rsquo;s%20production%20methods%20(e.g.,%20purchasing%20stationery%20that%20is%20a%20standard%20product%20of%20the%20supplier).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIf%20the%20organization%20cannot%20report%20exact%20figures,%20it%20can%20report%20estimates%20of%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20to%20the%20nearest%20ten%20or,%20where%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20is%20greater%20than%201,000,%20to%20the%20nearest%20100,%20and%20explain%20this%20under%202-8-b.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20to%202-8-a-i%20and%202-8-a-ii%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20reporting%20its%20contractual%20relationship%20with%20the%20most%20common%20types%20of%20workers,%20the%20organization%20should%20report%20whether%20it%20engages%20them%20directly%20or%20indirectly%20through%20a%20third%20party,%20and%20in%20the%20latter%20case,%20who%20this%20third%20party%20is%20(e.g.,%20employment%20agency,%20contractor).%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIt%20is%20sufficient%20that%20the%20organization%20provides%20a%20general%20description.%20The%20organization%20is%20not%20required%20to%20report%20the%20type%20of%20worker,%20contractual%20relationship,%20and%20work%20performed%20for%20every%20worker%20who%20is%20not%20an%20employee.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20to%202-8-b%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EThe%20organization%20can%20report%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20in%20head%20count%20or%20full-time%20equivalent%20(FTE).%20The%20head%20count%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20number%20of%20individual%20workers,%20whether%20on%20a%20full-time%20or%20part-time%20basis.%20The%20FTE%20gives%20insight%20into%20the%20hours%20worked.%20The%20organization%20can%20use%20another%20methodology%20for%20reporting%20this%20number.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EReporting%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20reporting%20period%20provides%20information%20for%20that%20point%20in%20time&nbsp;%20without%20capturing%20fluctuations%20during%20the%20reporting%20period.%20Reporting%20this%20number%20as%20an%20average%20across%20the%20reporting%20period%20takes%20into%20account%20fluctuations%20during%20the%20reporting%20period.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E&nbsp;%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuidance%20to%202-8-c%3C/strong%3E%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3ERequirement%202-8-c%20enables%20the%20organization%20to%20explain%20how%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20varies%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20or%20compared%20to%20previous%20reporting%20periods%20(i.e.,%20whether%20the%20numbers%20have%20increased%20or%20decreased).%20It%20can%20also%20include%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20fluctuations.%20For%20example,%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20during%20the%20reporting%20period%20could%20be%20due%20to%20a%20seasonal%20event.%20Conversely,%20a%20decrease%20in%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20employees%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20reporting%20period%20could%20be%20due%20to%20the%20completion%20of%20a%20temporary%20project.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3EIt%20is%20up%20to%20the%20organization%20to%20determine%20which%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20it%20considers%20significant%20to%20report%20under%202-8-c.%20The%20organization%20should%20report%20its%20threshold%20for%20determining%20significant%20fluctuations.%3C/div%3E%0A%3Cdiv%3